Bobby...

255
00:13:06,467 --> 00:13:08,300
Let's go see Tootsie
in the dressing room.

256
00:13:09,467 --> 00:13:12,300
Let's take Bobby with us.
She's all alone here.

257
00:13:12,433 --> 00:13:14,067
Do you want to, Bobby?

258
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:15,733
- Oh, okay.
- So you can meet our friend.

259
00:13:15,867 --> 00:13:16,933
- Okay.
- Oh, come on, come on.

260
00:13:17,067 --> 00:13:18,000
We'll collect payment.

261
00:13:18,133 --> 00:13:19,300
Yes, come on, come on, let's go.

262
00:13:19,433 --> 00:13:21,567
- These guys are embarrassing.
- You're always hungry.

263
00:13:21,733 --> 00:13:23,400
Hello?

264
00:13:23,533 --> 00:13:25,100
Alma, you called.

265
00:13:25,233 --> 00:13:27,367
Sorry, it's noisy where I am.

266
00:13:27,500 --> 00:13:30,967
No, it's okay, Sir. Listen.
I had another vision.

267
00:13:31,100 --> 00:13:33,300
I don't know if what
I'm telling you makes sense,

268
00:13:33,433 --> 00:13:35,567
but I saw the killer.

269
00:13:35,700 --> 00:13:39,467
He was inside a place
with people laughing.

270
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:42,033
And I also saw the stiletto
with neon lights.

271
00:13:42,167 --> 00:13:43,933
Are you sure about
what you're saying?

272
00:13:44,067 --> 00:13:46,267
Yes, I'm serious, Sir Tonyo!

273
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:49,133
It's up to you whether you
believe me or not!

274
00:13:49,267 --> 00:13:52,167
But the killer
killed another gay man,

275
00:13:52,300 --> 00:13:54,033
and he has a birthmark
on his hand!

276
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:56,833
I just don't remember his face.

277
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:00,233
Yes!

278
00:14:00,367 --> 00:14:02,000
We'll just go to the CR.

279
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:06,400
Hey...

280
00:14:07,433 --> 00:14:09,233
Cecilia might get bored.
What's this about?

281
00:14:09,367 --> 00:14:10,767
Can you stop?

282
00:14:10,900 --> 00:14:11,900
Why?

283
00:14:12,033 --> 00:14:13,933
Why, do you think I don't know
what you're doing?

284
00:14:14,067 --> 00:14:16,567
You're using me to make
the doctor jealous, right?

285
00:14:18,867 --> 00:14:20,667
You know, what you're doing
to me is wrong.

286
00:14:23,767 --> 00:14:26,467
Before, I just let you tease me.

287
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:27,933
But now, not anymore.

288
00:14:29,200 --> 00:14:31,267
Is it because you found out what
my price was at the auction.

289
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:32,933
That's why you're treating me
like that?

290
00:14:37,133 --> 00:14:38,267
That's why you're insulting me?

291
00:14:38,400 --> 00:14:40,167
You're rude to me!

292
00:14:40,300 --> 00:14:43,400
I'll accept your teasing,
but this, no more.

293
00:14:43,900 --> 00:14:46,867
You're even using me
to make the other girl jealous.

294
00:14:48,767 --> 00:14:50,833
Is that how low you think of me?

295
00:14:55,367 --> 00:14:58,533
Is that why you invited me here?

296
00:14:58,667 --> 00:14:59,833
Selena...

297
00:15:01,767 --> 00:15:03,267
let me explain.

298
00:15:06,267 --> 00:15:07,500
You don't have to.

299
00:15:13,067 --> 00:15:15,067
I don't know if what you're
saying is true,

300
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:17,667
but thank you.

301
00:15:19,100 --> 00:15:20,567
- Okay.
- Mister,

302
00:15:20,700 --> 00:15:24,467
I need some cold water, please.
Thank you!

303
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:26,533
Hey, because of you,
my wife and I had a fight!

304
00:15:26,667 --> 00:15:28,667
- What's with you?
- You should apologize!

305
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:29,733
- Why should I apologize?
- Apologize!

306
00:15:29,867 --> 00:15:30,833
It was just a joke!

307
00:15:30,967 --> 00:15:32,400
You're here at a comedy bar!

308
00:15:32,533 --> 00:15:35,033
If you don't get it,
I wish you hadn't come here!

309
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:36,800
Brad, Brad,
what's going on here?

310
00:15:36,933 --> 00:15:38,000
I'm a policeman.

311
00:15:38,133 --> 00:15:39,733
Sir, I'm just going to teach
this guy a lesson, Sir.

312
00:15:39,867 --> 00:15:41,900
It was just a joke, Mister!

313
00:15:42,033 --> 00:15:43,467
You don't get it!

314
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:45,633
If you do anything stupid here,

315
00:15:45,767 --> 00:15:47,733
I'll have to take you
to the precinct.

316
00:15:55,767 --> 00:15:56,833
Sir, thank you.

317
00:15:56,967 --> 00:15:58,400
- Are you okay?
- Yes.

318
00:15:58,533 --> 00:15:59,433
Thank you, Sir.

319
00:16:01,100 --> 00:16:03,467
- Tootsie!
- Tootsie!

320
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:06,233
Don't disturb him.
I think he's resting.

321
00:16:06,367 --> 00:16:07,833
That's okay!

322
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:10,000
We only come here
once in a while!

323
00:16:10,133 --> 00:16:12,367
And I know him.
Because he owes us something.

324
00:16:12,500 --> 00:16:13,267
That's right.

325
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:14,167
He's just pretending
to be asleep.

326
00:16:14,300 --> 00:16:15,233
It's true!

327
00:16:15,367 --> 00:16:16,400
Let's go!

328
00:16:16,533 --> 00:16:18,867
- Hey, it's embarrassing.
- He's just acting, yeah.

329
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:20,600
Yeah, and he was great earlier.

330
00:16:20,733 --> 00:16:22,667
- Hey! Gay!
- Tootsie!

331
00:16:25,567 --> 00:16:27,067
Bobby...

332
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:29,900
- Abdul, take Mar outside!
- Mar...

333
00:16:30,033 --> 00:16:31,100
Hey, Mar!

334
00:16:35,233 --> 00:16:36,367
Ma'am Cecilia...

335
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:39,633
Sorry, but did I interrupt you?

336
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:44,600
No, Eric is so sweet.

337
00:16:44,733 --> 00:16:46,000
I wasn't able to control myself.

338
00:16:47,467 --> 00:16:49,733
Well, I'm happy for both of you.

339
00:16:49,867 --> 00:16:51,400
Will you still go to the CR?

340
00:16:51,533 --> 00:16:52,833
No, I'm done.

341
00:16:52,967 --> 00:16:54,533
- Okay, I'll just use the CR.
- Okay.

342
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:07,367
Hello, Bobby.

343
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:08,367
Hello, Tonyo!

344
00:17:08,500 --> 00:17:10,267
Come to the dressing room now.

345
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:12,133
There's a performer dead!

346
00:17:12,267 --> 00:17:13,300
What?

347
00:17:14,633 --> 00:17:15,667
Okay, okay.

348
00:17:18,600 --> 00:17:21,667
Brad, Lieutenant Antonio Conde
of Station 12.

349
00:17:22,767 --> 00:17:25,000
Don't let anyone out, okay?

350
00:17:25,133 --> 00:17:26,100
Why, Sir?

351
00:17:27,600 --> 00:17:28,700
That's it.

352
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:34,567
Hello?

353
00:17:34,700 --> 00:17:36,933
This is Master Sergeant
Bobby Enriquez.

354
00:17:37,067 --> 00:17:39,433
I'm here at the Stiletto
Comedy Bar.

355
00:17:39,567 --> 00:17:42,067
Requesting for SOCO and backup
immediately.

356
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:43,133
Okay, thank you.

357
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:55,067
Bobby!

358
00:17:55,200 --> 00:17:56,067
Tonyo!

359
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:57,633
I've locked down the whole bar.

360
00:17:59,433 --> 00:18:00,533
What happened?

361
00:18:00,667 --> 00:18:03,167
Mar and Abdul
went to see his friend.

362
00:18:03,300 --> 00:18:04,867
When we got here,
that's what happened.

363
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:11,367
Go, Peach, you can do it.

364
00:18:11,500 --> 00:18:12,433
That's it.

365
00:18:14,667 --> 00:18:16,267
What's with you, Bessie?

366
00:18:16,400 --> 00:18:17,933
You failed to shoot the ball.

367
00:18:18,067 --> 00:18:21,933
Yeah, but seriously,
it's fun to play billiards.

368
00:18:22,100 --> 00:18:23,000
That's right, Apple,

369
00:18:23,133 --> 00:18:27,033
but it's hard to hit the balls
with sticks.

370
00:18:31,533 --> 00:18:32,533
What?

371
00:18:33,467 --> 00:18:36,400
Are you going to make up for it,
or are you giving up?

372
00:18:36,533 --> 00:18:38,200
Me, no.

373
00:18:38,333 --> 00:18:39,300
I have to go.

374
00:18:40,333 --> 00:18:41,767
Faye, I'll go ahead.

375
00:18:41,900 --> 00:18:42,967
Thank you, Cecilia.

376
00:18:43,100 --> 00:18:44,033
Thank you.

377
00:18:44,167 --> 00:18:46,233
- Bye!
- Take care.

378
00:18:46,367 --> 00:18:47,433
Eric,

379
00:18:47,567 --> 00:18:48,967
Selena.

380
00:18:49,100 --> 00:18:50,600
See you.

381
00:18:50,733 --> 00:18:51,967
Thank you, Cecilia!

382
00:18:54,233 --> 00:18:55,367
Okay, thank you very much.

383
00:18:55,533 --> 00:18:59,067
Just make sure all the staff
and customers stay here, okay?

384
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:00,467
- Yes, Sir.
- Okay, Boss.

385
00:19:03,500 --> 00:19:06,533
Oh my, Dude, Tootsie was killed.

386
00:19:06,667 --> 00:19:08,533
That's right.
What happened?

387
00:19:08,667 --> 00:19:10,100
I don't know either, Dude.

388
00:19:10,233 --> 00:19:11,800
Let's just follow Sir.

389
00:19:11,933 --> 00:19:12,800
That's right.

390
00:19:12,933 --> 00:19:14,700
Come on,
you can check over there.

391
00:19:14,833 --> 00:19:16,300
What, Jade, did you enjoy
yourself?

392
00:19:16,433 --> 00:19:17,833
Let's go back here.
That was fun.

393
00:19:17,967 --> 00:19:19,000
What, Faye?

394
00:19:19,133 --> 00:19:21,200
Did you text your driver?

395
00:19:21,333 --> 00:19:22,267
Yes.

396
00:19:23,233 --> 00:19:25,033
Allan, thank you.

397
00:19:25,167 --> 00:19:28,467
Anyway, my sadness about losing
daddy has lessened.

398
00:19:29,933 --> 00:19:31,200
I'm glad you're happy.

399
00:19:31,333 --> 00:19:34,600
Didn't I tell you, we can date
here at the billiards every day?

400
00:19:35,633 --> 00:19:37,833
Sure, sure.

401
00:19:37,967 --> 00:19:41,233
-Faye, come with me to CR first.
-Come on. Just wait.

402
00:19:41,367 --> 00:19:42,067
Okay, we'll stay here first.

403
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:43,900
- Okay.
- We'll wait for you.

404
00:19:46,833 --> 00:19:50,667
Dude, didn't you understand me,
or are you just teasing?

405
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:52,367
Maybe you're the one
who doesn't understand.

406
00:19:52,500 --> 00:19:54,800
Didn't I ask you if Faye
was your girlfriend?

407
00:19:54,933 --> 00:19:56,467
You told me no, right?

408
00:19:57,100 --> 00:19:59,500
But you behaved like she
was your girlfriend.

409
00:19:59,633 --> 00:20:01,233
You're the one who's been
touching her.

410
00:20:01,400 --> 00:20:02,533
You've been touching her
a lot earlier.

411
00:20:02,667 --> 00:20:03,867
Wait, wait, Dude.

412
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:05,300
What kind of touching?

413
00:20:05,433 --> 00:20:06,933
I'm just supporting the girl.

414
00:20:07,067 --> 00:20:08,267
You talk as if...

415
00:20:09,700 --> 00:20:10,733
Dude, stop it

416
00:20:10,867 --> 00:20:13,000
because I don't know what to do
with you anymore.

417
00:20:13,133 --> 00:20:14,567
You're the one
who should stop.

418
00:20:14,700 --> 00:20:16,633
If you feel like
I'm ahead of you,

419
00:20:16,767 --> 00:20:17,900
do you know what that means?

420
00:20:18,967 --> 00:20:20,367
You're not her type,

421
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:21,167
Jerk.

422
00:20:24,333 --> 00:20:25,467
Have a drink first, Mar.

423
00:20:29,700 --> 00:20:30,467
Sir,

424
00:20:31,167 --> 00:20:33,267
when we saw Tootsie,

425
00:20:34,967 --> 00:20:36,300
I couldn't handle it.

426
00:20:38,333 --> 00:20:40,767
It was the first time I've seen
something like that.

427
00:20:40,900 --> 00:20:43,533
That's why I fainted.

428
00:20:44,133 --> 00:20:45,367
How about you?

429
00:20:45,500 --> 00:20:47,233
Have you worked with Tootsie
for a long time?

430
00:20:47,367 --> 00:20:50,467
Sir, I've worked with Tootsie
for a long time.

431
00:20:50,600 --> 00:20:53,133
In fact, we're like siblings.

432
00:20:53,267 --> 00:20:56,233
And I don't think
he has an enemy

433
00:20:56,367 --> 00:20:58,100
or a grudge against anyone.

434
00:21:05,800 --> 00:21:07,033
It's been a long time.

435
00:21:07,167 --> 00:21:09,033
My husband has been looking
for me.

436
00:21:11,133 --> 00:21:14,033
I haven't even found
anything yet, so I can't leave.

437
00:21:15,567 --> 00:21:17,433
That's why.

438
00:21:17,567 --> 00:21:19,433
Do you know?

439
00:21:19,567 --> 00:21:22,433
I heard someone
was killed inside.

440
00:21:22,567 --> 00:21:23,767
Really?

441
00:21:23,900 --> 00:21:25,067
Who?

442
00:21:25,200 --> 00:21:26,500
Let me guess.

443
00:21:26,633 --> 00:21:30,467
Two customers, they were drunk
and got into a fight.

444
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:32,033
What was that?

445
00:21:32,167 --> 00:21:34,567
When you entered the dressing
room, Tootsie was dead?

446
00:21:34,700 --> 00:21:36,067
Yes, Chief.

447
00:21:36,200 --> 00:21:39,367
Then I called Lieutenant Conde.

448
00:21:39,500 --> 00:21:41,533
I also spoke to the bouncer,
Chief.

449
00:21:41,700 --> 00:21:43,867
Don't let anyone out.

450
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:47,633
Maybe the killer is among
the customers.

451
00:21:47,767 --> 00:21:50,333
All right, Conde.

452
00:21:50,467 --> 00:21:52,200
Interview all the customers.

453
00:21:52,333 --> 00:21:54,100
Maybe we can get some
information.

454
00:21:54,233 --> 00:21:55,733
Maybe the killer
is just around.

455
00:21:55,867 --> 00:21:57,600
- Yes, Sir.
- Okay.

456
00:21:57,733 --> 00:21:58,733
Enriquez.

457
00:21:58,867 --> 00:22:00,133
Sir?

458
00:22:00,267 --> 00:22:01,367
Follow me.

459
00:22:10,133 --> 00:22:13,333
Sir, what do you want me to do?

460
00:22:13,467 --> 00:22:17,000
Enriquez, you're on leave,
right?

461
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:20,033
You can go home now.

462
00:22:20,167 --> 00:22:22,800
But, Sir, I'm fine.

463
00:22:22,933 --> 00:22:24,867
I want to help find the killer.

464
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:28,633
Enriquez, your father just died.

465
00:22:28,767 --> 00:22:31,300
Sir, we need everyone on deck.

466
00:22:31,433 --> 00:22:33,267
You need a lot of people now.

467
00:22:33,400 --> 00:22:35,333
The killer is still at large.
We haven't seen him yet.

468
00:22:35,467 --> 00:22:39,300
Enriquez, that's not a request.

469
00:22:39,433 --> 00:22:41,267
Go home, go ahead.

470
00:22:47,267 --> 00:22:48,467
Jerk?

471
00:22:51,533 --> 00:22:52,733
That's enough!

472
00:22:57,133 --> 00:22:59,300
That's enough!
Vince, that's enough!

473
00:22:59,433 --> 00:23:00,300
Let go of me!

474
00:23:04,967 --> 00:23:05,933
Bobby...

475
00:23:07,167 --> 00:23:08,500
What did Chief say?

476
00:23:08,633 --> 00:23:10,267
He's sending me home.

477
00:23:10,400 --> 00:23:13,067
You need a lot of people now,
right?

478
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:15,100
Talk to Chief.

479
00:23:15,233 --> 00:23:16,467
Maybe...

480
00:23:16,600 --> 00:23:18,367
Maybe Chief is right.

481
00:23:18,500 --> 00:23:19,733
What do you mean?

482
00:23:19,867 --> 00:23:24,967
Aren't you on leave now
because you lost a loved one?

483
00:23:27,933 --> 00:23:32,400
I told you, you need a break.

484
00:23:32,533 --> 00:23:35,167
Don't you really want to believe
that I'm okay?

485
00:23:37,400 --> 00:23:40,500
Well, if you don't need my help

486
00:23:40,633 --> 00:23:43,233
and you don't want to believe
that I'm okay.

487
00:23:43,367 --> 00:23:44,600
Well, I'll just go home.

488
00:23:44,733 --> 00:23:46,533
- No, no, it's not like that.
- No, it's okay.

489
00:23:46,667 --> 00:23:47,333
No, okay, I'll just talk
to Chief!

490
00:23:47,467 --> 00:23:48,967
No need! I'm going home! No!

491
00:23:53,500 --> 00:23:56,633
Mar, Abdul, come on,
let's go home.

492
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:57,867
Sir.

493
00:24:16,733 --> 00:24:18,467
Looks like you need to tell him
the truth.

494
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:20,767
Vince, I did you wrong.

495
00:24:20,900 --> 00:24:21,900
That was my first time.

496
00:24:22,033 --> 00:24:22,900
What first time?

497
00:24:23,033 --> 00:24:24,600
That was my first kiss earlier.

498
00:24:24,733 --> 00:24:26,800
I wanted to talk to you
about my late father.

499
00:24:26,933 --> 00:24:28,033
What about it, Glen?

500
00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:31,200
You know, when I asked you
to help me with the situation...

501
00:24:31,333 --> 00:24:33,433
I just wanted to know
if Joaquin's inheritance

502
00:24:33,567 --> 00:24:35,867
from that intruder
can still be recovered.

503
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:41,033
Make sure that woman
won't get anything.

504
00:24:41,300 --> 00:24:42,433
Noble, where is the guy
we're chasing?

505
00:24:42,567 --> 00:24:43,900
Well, Sir, he's escaping.

506
00:24:44,033 --> 00:24:45,000
How did he escape?

507
00:24:45,133 --> 00:24:46,567
Ma'am Bobby bumped into him.
